<FILEID>AP-NR-12-12-89 0134EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a PM-BoxOffice     12-12 0421</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Box Office,0438</SECOND>
<HEAD>`War of the Roses' Wins Box Office Battle for First Place</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JEFF WILSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``The War of the Roses'' narrowly won the
weekend box office battle, easing ahead of ``National Lampoon's
Christmas Vacation'' by less than $200,000.
   ``The War of the Roses,'' a dark comedy about marital hatred
starring Michael Douglas, Kathleen Turner and Danny DeVito, came
out on top with $9.7 million. ``Christmas Vacation,'' starring
Chevy Chase, finished with $9.5 million.
   ``It's one of the tighter races in a long time,'' said John
Krier of Exhibitor Relations Co., which tracks box office
performance.
   ``Back to the Future Part II'' dropped to third place, taking in
$7 million in its third week of release. The Michael J. Fox
time-warp fantasy has accumulated nearly $70 million since
Thanksgiving Eve.
   The fourth-place, $3.5 million debut of ``She-Devil'' was a
disappointment, despite what appeared to be the sure-fire hit
pairing of Oscar-winner Meryl Streep and TV's Roseanne Barr in her
first movie role.
   ``Steel Magnolias'' was fifth with $3 million and ``Harlem
Nights'' was sixth with $2.9 million.
   Disney's ``The Little Mermaid'' feature-length cartoon earned
$2.8 million for seventh place, followed by ``Look Who's Talking,''
with $2.5 million.
   ``Prancer'' was in ninth with $1.7 million and the season's
other animated release, ``All Dogs Go To Heaven,'' rounded out the
top 10 with $1.5 million.
   Here are the top movie ticket sales for Friday through Sunday as
tallied by Entertainment Data and Exhibitor Relations.
   1. ``The War of the Roses,'' 20th Century Fox, $9.69 million
(weekend gross), 1,259 screens, $7,696 per screen, $9.69 million
(total gross), one week in release.
   2. ``National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation,'' Warner Bros.,
$9.49 million, 1,744 screens, $5,447 per screen, $24.3 million, two
weeks.
   3. ``Back to the Future Part II,'' Universal, $7.01 million,
1,986 screens, $3,530 per screen, $69.49 million, three weeks.
   4. ``She-Devil,'' Orion, $3.51 million, 1,403 screens, $2,502
per screen, $3.51 million, one week.
   5. ``Steel Magnolias,'' Tri-Star, $3.02 million, 1,032 screens,
$2,928 per screen, $27.47 million, four weeks.
   6. ``Harlem Nights,'' Paramount, $2.92 million, 2,180 screens,
$1,338 per screen, $46.88 million, four weeks.
   7. ``The Little Mermaid,'' Disney, $2.76 million, 999 screens,
$2,767 per screen, $25.75 million, four weeks.
   8. ``Look Who's Talking,'' Tri-Star, $2.52 million, 1,645
screens, $1,535 per screen, $104.94 million, nine weeks.
   9. ``Prancer,'' Orion, $1.65 million, 1,659 screens, $996 per
screen, $12.75 million, four weeks.
   10. ``All Dogs Go to Heaven,'' MGM-UA, $1.53 million, 1,572
screens, $972 per screen, $16.10 million, four weeks.
</TEXT>
