   John Z. De Lorean is still tied up in
lawsuits stemming from the bankruptcy of his car company, but he
says things are looking up five years after his acquittal on
cocaine-trafficking charges.
   The 64-year-old carmaker says he's back on good terms with his
former wife, Cristina Ferrare, after a bitter divorce. He said he's
dating someone else, but the reconciliation with Ms. Ferrare
improves life for their children.
   De Lorean sees an end to the lawsuits that have been holding up
his plans to start producing another super-luxury car.
   ``All these things, if they don't kill you they make you
stronger,'' he said Friday in a telephone interview from New York.
   He's enthusiastic about the planned new car, which he hopes to
