<HEAD>Border Guards Placed Under Police Control</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Romania's hard-line Communist leadership
has put its border guards under police supervision, the Romanian
state news agency reported today.
   Agerpres gave few details but it appeared the move was meant to
stop the growing number of illegal crossings by citizens fleeing
political repression and economic hardship.
   Former Olympic gymnast Nadia Comaneci defected on Nov. 30 and
now is in the United States.
   The Communist Party's ruling Politburo met Monday and decided to
transfer border guard units from the Ministry of National Defense
``to the subordination of the Ministry of the Interior,'' Agerpres
said.
   Other Romanians who fled across the border into Hungary recently
included eight shepherds and their herd of 1,140 sheep.
