<HEAD>Windsor Ridenour Named Executive Editor at Tulsa Paper</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TULSA, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Windsor Ridenour, managing editor of The
Tulsa Tribune since 1982, has been appointed executive editor and
will concentrate on research and long-range planning.
   In other appointments announced late last month, Pearl Wittkopp,
city editor, has been named managing editor for news and Mary
Hargrove has been named managing editor for special projects.
   Ms. Wittkopp will oversee various departments and handle
recruiting and hiring.
   Mary Hargrove, who has headed the newspaper's investigative
team, will continue her duties but also will train reporters in how
to work with public documents.
