<HEAD>Pope Accepts Orlando Resignation, Appoints Duluth Bishop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II on Tuesday accepted the
resignation of the bishop of Orlando, Fla., and appointed a new
bishop in Duluth, Minn., the Vatican said.
   Orlando Bishop Thomas J. Grady turned 75, the usual retirement
age, on Oct. 9. His successor was not announced.
