<FIRST>r w AM-Yeutter-Poland     12-12 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Yeutter-Poland,190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Yeutter Says Poland Wants Pesticides Targeted in U.S.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Items Poland needs to whip food inflation
include chemical pesticides that have been targeted by federal
regulators and environmentalists, Agriculture Secretary Clayton
Yeutter said Tuesday.
   ``We need to do whatever we can to improve agricultural
productivity in Poland,'' Yeutter told the National Press Club.
``Interestingly, there were two principle requests in this area.''
   The major requests were high-protein supplements for livestock
feed and agricultural chemicals.
   ``As we have experienced the situation here where folks are
wanting to ban agricultural chemicals in the United States, the No.
1 priority on the list in Poland was agricultural chemicals,'' he
said.
   But the aid package approved by Congress doesn't include such
chemicals.
   ``There's little that we can do, perhaps nothing that we can do
in the way of agricultural chemicals from a governmental
standpoint,'' Yeutter said, adding that the private sector may have
to meet Poland's request for farm chemicals through grants and
donations.
   Yeutter recently led a presidential mission to Poland to help
determine what kind of aid is needed to help that country rebuild
its agriculture.
