<SECOND>BC-The '80s-Top 10 List, Adv 16,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv16</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Weekend Editions Dec. 16-17 and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>With The '80s-Top 10 Stories</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the top 10 news stories of the decade, as voted on by
editors and news directors of member newspapers and broadcast
stations of The Associated Press. The 306 respondents ranked the
stories in descending order, with 10 points for first place and one
point for 10th place.
   The list, and the scores each received:
   
   1. Gorbachev's rise and the decline of East European communism,
2,593.
   2. The AIDS epidemic, 1,830.
   3. The Reagan presidency: tax cuts, cuts in social programs,
economic growth, 1,138.
   4. Drug addiction and attendant crime, 1,050.
   5. The promise of the space shuttle; the disaster of Challenger,
860.
   6. Terrorism, including Iran hostage crisis, 720.
   7. Chernobyl nuclear plant explosion, 700.
   8. China: liberalization, then crushing of democratic movement,
661.
   9. Iran-Contra affair, 503.
   10. Central American wars, 442.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv Weekend Editions Dec. 16-17 and Thereafter</NOTE>
