<FIRST>r f PM-SavingsBonds     12-12 0088</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Savings Bonds,0092</SECOND>
<HEAD>Buy $541 Million in Savings Bonds in November</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sales of U.S. savings bonds totaled $541
million in November, bringing to $116.96 billion the value of such
bonds held by Aemricans, the Treasury Department reported.
   Sales for the first two months of fiscal year 1990, which began
Oct. 1, totaled $1.13 billion, the same amount sold during October
and November, 1988, the Treasury said Monday.
   Savings bonds currently earn interest at a rate of 6.98 percent
when held five years or longer.
</TEXT>
