   The stock market shot higher late today as oil
stocks led an afternoon rally.
   At 3 p.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones average of 30
industrials was up 15.15 to 2,743.39.
   Advances outnumbered declines in nationwide trading of New York
Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 810 up, 673 down and 509
unchanged. Volume on the Big Board came to 144 million shares with
one hour to go.
   Analysts said large block purchases of oil company stocks pushed
the market above the narrow trading ranges that characterized the
earlier part of the day, when the Dow was up slightly but losers
outpaced gainers.
   ``It looks like a pretty big rush to the plate with oils,'' said
Eugene Peroni of Janney Montgomery Scott Inc. in Philadelphia. ``I
think there's a perception that oil prices are going to be moving
higher next year.''
