computerized program trading.
   Otherwise, traders said the market generally was biding time
until the release on Friday of reports on the producer price index
for November and the October trade deficit. Friday also brings
expiration of stock-index futures and options.
   In the national over-the-counter market, Apple Computer was down
2{ to 36} in heavy trading. The company projected an earnings
decline and slowing sales growth for the first quarter of fiscal
1990.
   The announcement dragged down other technology issues, as well
as the broader over-the-counter market.
   Intel was down [ to 32\, Compaq fell | to 81 after a weak
earnings forecast, International Business Machines was up { to 96|,
Hewlett-Packard lost [ to 45| and Digital Equipment up ] to 84].
   Among other heavily traded Big Board stocks, American Telephone
&amp; Telegraph was up | to 45, one day after announcing job cuts that
could total more than 30,000.
